Project Report: local-store-ecom

Purpose
This is a small e-commerce starter project named "local-store-ecom". It demonstrates a simple online store with a React frontend and a Node.js backend. It supports storing products, customers, and orders using MongoDB (primary) or MySQL (optional).

What the project does (simple)
- Shows a product catalog on the frontend.
- Provides backend API endpoints to list, create, update, and delete products and manage orders.
- Includes a manual seed script to populate the database with example products.

Technology stack
- Backend: Node.js (ES modules), Express
- Database: MongoDB (preferred) or MySQL
- ORM/driver: Mongoose for MongoDB, mysql2 for MySQL
- Frontend: React + Vite
- Config: dotenv

Important files and folders
- backend/server.js — main Express server
- backend/models/mongodb/productModel.js — MongoDB product model and CRUD functions
- backend/scripts/addProducts.js — seed script (manual) to add example products
- backend/scripts/checkProducts.js — script to list products from DB
- backend/scripts/sample help.txt — short instructions for seeding
- frontend/ — React/Vite app with components (ProductList, Cart, Checkout, Admin pages)

How product seeding works (simple explanation)
- The seed script is manual. Run it only when you want to add or clean product data.
- Edit the `products` array in `backend/scripts/addProducts.js` to add or change sample products.
- Run `node scripts/addProducts.js` from the `backend` folder to process products.
- The script reads DB settings from `backend/.env`:
  - If `DB_TYPE=mongodb`, it writes to MongoDB using `MONGODB_URI`.
  - Otherwise it attempts MySQL using DB_HOST/DB_USER/DB_PASSWORD/DB_NAME.

Duplicate handling
- Before inserting, the script checks if a product with the same `name` exists.
- If duplicates are found, it keeps the newest entry and removes older copies.
- If a product already exists (single entry), the script skips adding a new one.
- New products are added only when no matching name exists.

